  "messages": [
    {
      "id": "3dfc6ffc70448eeb19e3d4a588899a4130b18cc9",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-04 01:21:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nChris, while it may be true that there is a small semantic issue that the lustre-ldiskfs package is not actually built from the lustre.spec file, but I think this change will confuse a larger number of end users that expect to be able to do \"rpm -Fvh lustre-*\" and get all of their lustre packages upgraded.  True, the spec files are not related, but ldiskfs is definitely part of Lustre and to me it makes sense that the name reflect this. \n\nI've added James and John as inspectors to get some more opinions on what is more important to end users.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
